YAMLJSONXML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>hello: "Hello World!"
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.yaml</code>: <pre><code>hello: "Bonjour le monde!"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{"hello": "Hello World!"}
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.json</code>: <pre><code>{"hello": "Bonjour le monde!"}
</code></pre></p> <p>Note</p> <p>The root element is ignored in XML files. See Supported Formats for details.</p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Hello World!&lt;/hello&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Bonjour le monde!&lt;/hello&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p>

YAMLJSONXML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>cat:
    one: "{count} cat"
    other: "{count} cats"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    "cat": {
        "one": "{count} cat",
        "other": "{count} cats"
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;cat&gt;
        &lt;one&gt;{count} cat&lt;/one&gt;
        &lt;other&gt;{count} cats&lt;/other&gt;
    &lt;/cat&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Usage:</p> <pre><code>from doti18n import LocaleData

i18n = LocaleData("locales")

print(i18n["en"].cat(1))   # Output: 1 cat
print(i18n["en"].cat(3))   # Output: 3 cats
print(i18n["en"].cat(11))  # Output: 11 cats
</code></pre>

YAMLJSONXML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>:</p> <pre><code># key-value
hello: "Hello World!"

# list
fruits:
    - "Apple"
    - "Banana"
    - "Orange"

# nested list
items:
    - name: "Item 1" 
    - name: "Item 2"

# nested dict
errors:
    connection: "Connection error occurred."
    timeout: "Request timed out."

# pluralization
notifications:
    one: "You have {count} new notification."
    other: "You have {count} new notifications."
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard YAML features (anchors, aliases, complex structures) are fully supported.</p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    // key-value
    "hello": "Hello World!",

    // list
    "fruits": [
        "Apple",
        "Banana",
        "Orange"
    ],        

    // nested list
    "items": [
        {"name": "Item 1"},
        {"name": "Item 2"}
    ],

    // nested dict
    "errors": {
        "connection": "Connection error occurred.",
        "timeout": "Request timed out."
    },

    // pluralization
    "notifications": {
        "one": "You have {count} new notification.",
        "other": "You have {count} new notifications."
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard JSON does not support comments. The comments above are for illustration only.</p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;!-- key-value --&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Hello World!&lt;/hello&gt;

    &lt;!-- list --&gt;
    &lt;fruits list="true"&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Apple&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Banana&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Orange&lt;/fruit&gt;
    &lt;/fruits&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested list --&gt;
    &lt;items list="true"&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 1&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 2&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
    &lt;/items&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested dict --&gt;
    &lt;errors&gt;
        &lt;connection&gt;Connection error occurred.&lt;/connection&gt;
        &lt;timeout&gt;Request timed out.&lt;/timeout&gt;
    &lt;/errors&gt;

    &lt;!-- pluralization --&gt;
    &lt;notifications&gt;
        &lt;one&gt;You have {count} new notification.&lt;/one&gt;
        &lt;other&gt;You have {count} new notifications.&lt;/other&gt;
    &lt;/notifications&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>XML Parsing Logic</p> <ul> <li>Root Element: Ignored. You can name it anything (e.g., <code>&lt;locale&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;data&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;xml&gt;</code>), it serves only as a container.</li> <li>Lists: Tags with identical child names are automatically treated as lists.</li> <li>Explicit Lists: To force a list (e.g., for a single element), add the <code>list="true"</code> attribute to the parent tag. Using <code>list="true"</code> explicitly is recommended for consistency.</li> </ul>
